<Author>russ_brighton
<Content>a great place to stay In December 2008 I took a tour from Bangkok to Singapore - which ended at The Royal Peacock Hotel - one night - as part of the tour. I wanted to stay an extra night but the rates were too high so I looked for an alternative. I stumbled upon Hotel 1929 and I'm so pleased I did. When we checked into the Peacock I noticed that it was directly opposite the 1929 and as there was no wireless internet access in the Peacock I went over the road to check whether they had access at 1929. The staff were just so helpful - they confirmed that they do have wirelss access in the hotel lobby and after checking my reservation for the following day gave me access to the wireless broadband a day early. A Small thing, I know, but it's the small things that make a big difference. The rooms are very small - but also very comfortable. The staff are incredibly friendly and the place is spotless. It is a VERY modern hotel so someone looking for something more traditional won't find it here. Unfortunately, the terrace and jacuzzi were closed due to a breakdown when I was there - but they had people working to fix the problem asap - even though it was Christmas day. A great place to stay! 
