<Content>Cosy room in a good location I was rather apprehensive in choosing this hotel after reading the mixed reviews. However, given the budget that I had, decided to give it a shot. Overall, I would say that it exceeded my expectations. I stayed in a single superior room end July for three nights and was charged SGD170++ per night. Room - It was much smaller that the rooms that I was used to, but it was cosy and adequate. The design was certainly hip and the bed was very comfy.Location - Pretty good - five minutes walk to Outram Park MRT station. I felt safe walking from the station, even at about 11 pm. A taxi ride to Suntec City costs bot SGD9 (off-peak hours). There are some nearby small shopping malls and restaurants serving local cuisine. There is a Hindu temple near the hotel but I wasn't disturbed by the noise in the morning. However, I was awoken by the sound of nearby guests closing their doors bot 4am.Service - Booked the room via email. The receptionist was pretty helpful. Food - buffet breakfast consisted of cereal, fruits, juice, bread, meehoon, coffee or tea. Was also offered a plate of English breakfast - sausage, bacon, baked beans and eggs. Tried the set lunch at its restaurant, Ember which was very delicous. Priced at SGD38 ++, service was also wonderful and very efficient. They are open for lunch and dinner every weekday and only open for dinner on Sat. Closed for business on Sunday. Overall, it was a good experience. 
