<Author>Lightandbubbly2001
<Content>A home away from home My family and I stayed at this hotel for several days this July (July 9-12) since it was near the Singapore General Hospital where I had my checkup. There had been varying reviews to this hotel and I think it is because we have our own expectations and opinions. My family and I enjoyed our stay at the Hotel 1929. I called in to book our reservation to this hotel. The one who answered my queries and booking was very warm and courteous. This was unlike a staff of another hotel nearby who was very rude when I inquired over the phone. My reservation conservation came immediately and there was daily email from the staff with regards to our booking. We arrived on a midnight so we requested for a limousine service. Unfortunately the limousine driver missed us because our flight was delayed and there was a long queue at the immigration. The staff were very accomodating in resolving this problem.  Our room was small by standards but it was cozy. There is a water heater for bath, a small ref, internet connection, television, hairdryer, water heater, aircondition. Sheets were changed daily. There was a welcome note and chocolates from the General Manager and the Asst Manager for Concierge. We were able to sleep soundly, not distrurbed by the noise outside - this despite our room location (at the street corner). Staff was very warm and greeted us always with a smile, all with sunny personality. Thank you for your warm hospitality: to Ms Selria (whom I didnt get to meet personally - probably next time), Ms Angelia (Concierge), Winnie (Restaurant), Zawiyah, Hazley, Satinah, Amin (all from front desk), Ruen and Rashid (housekeeping, second floor). And of course, there was Bob, the bear. Hotel 1929 is our home away from home. It is walking distance to most stores in Chinatown like, to the famous Tiong Shan porridge restaurant, souvenir shops, a five minute walk to Outram Park MRT Station, Singapore General Hospital. Although it is a boutique hotel, you will have that sense of being brought back into time to the old Singapore, sans the high rise buildings... Hoping to visit you again soon 
