<Author>Msg_Singaporean
<Content>Can't Meet Its Obligations I am a Singaporean. I made reservations for 4 guests (2 rooms) at Hotel 1929, who arrived in Singapore on 7 Nov early morning. Reservation was confirmed directly to me by the hotel reservation staff, however when my guests arrived at the hotel, they were told that they is only 1 ROOM left !! I am very unsatisfied and fuming mad at the way the hotel staff handled the matter. As the rooms were not easily available during the past 1 week, we could only find 2 rooms at Robinson Hotel on Balestier Road (which is not convenient at all) for 2 nights. Thereafter, we had to search high  low for accommodation. Hotel 1929 didn't even offer to arrange transportation to send my 4 guests to the alternative accommodation. The guests took a cab to Robinson Hotel.One couple was here for honeymoon. They enjoyed themselves in Maldives and was throwm from heaven to hell !. I felt so sorry to my guests.So whoever wants to stay at this hotel (they have a newly opened hotel known as New Majestic Hotel), be prepared to be left in the lurch and take the risks of having to stay out on the street if you do not have any friends in Singapore. I hope this unhappy incident to happen to another innocent soul because I would be equally mad if such unhappy incident happen to me in a foreign land. This was reflected to the Singapore Tourism Board (STB) who only acts as a postbox to deliver my message to Hotel 1929. The STB is able to do nothing - so don't expect much ! Two compliments to Summer View Hotel. Even though Summer View is probably a 3 star hotel, I find that their service is very good :-(i) the staff offer to pack breakfast for my guests who need to leave the hotel at 5.30am to catch their flight. This is a very kind gesture of them.(ii) The uncle/security guard (I think he is in his 60s) who is working at the carpark behind the hotel highlighted to us that the exit door to the carpark would be shut after 11pm, so we had to leave from the front door. Wonderful service - much appreciated. 
