<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Great Hotel for Something Different I stayed at Hotel 1929 from March 17-20 in a Deluxe Room, and had a very good experience. Unlike many hotels, many 'extras' were included in the cost of my room--that means no additional charge for broadband internet, soft drinks and water in my fridge, and breakfast.The staff was very friendly and attentive, and genuinely wanted to make my stay an enjoyable one. Try to get a reservation at Ember, the restaurant next door--amazing!The downsides--I'd say my room was rather small, but also well designed, so that I never felt cramped. It's worth upgrading--I'd say they're 20% larger than the standard rooms. My only other gripe was that the room wasn't very soundproofed--I could hear trucks driving by at all hours, and people entering their rooms.I wanted some different than the generic chains seen throughout Singapore--and got it! It was a fun place to stay, with a GREAT location, and good service. However, if you're looking for the usual perks of a major chain--large rooms, a gym, quiet, etc., then you might want to look elsewhere. 
